
<section id="SigProcAmpMod">
  <title>Amplitude Modifiers and Dynamic processing</title>

  <para>
    The opcodes that modify amplitude are:
  </para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="balance"><citetitle>balance</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="balance2"><citetitle>balance2</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="compress"><citetitle>compress</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="compress2"><citetitle>compress2</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="clip"><citetitle>clip</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="dam"><citetitle>dam</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
      <listitem><para><link linkend="gain"><citetitle>gain</citetitle></link></para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  <para>The opcode <link linkend="Zerodbfs"><citetitle>0dbfs</citetitle></link> facilitates the use of amplitude by removing the need to use of explicit sample values.</para>

</section>
